1
00:00:00,799 --> 00:00:03,270
Trump declares a national emergency.

2
00:00:03,270 --> 00:00:06,240
It’s been dubbed the ‘Huawei ban’.

3
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:07,880
What does this mean for security?

4
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:11,600
And how will this affect Huawei’s global
ambitions?

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:17,500
Welcome back to China Uncensored.

6
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,949
I’m Chris Chappell.

7
00:00:18,949 --> 00:00:22,289
Last week, US President Donald Trump signed
an Executive Order

8
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:24,109
saying no way to Huawei.

9
00:00:24,109 --> 00:00:27,550
Well technically, it doesn't actually say
that.

10
00:00:27,550 --> 00:00:30,220
What it does say is "Executive Order on Securing

11
00:00:30,220 --> 00:00:32,570
the Information and Communications Technology

12
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:35,160
and Services Supply Chain."

13
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,899
But a title like that is totally un-tweetable.

14
00:00:37,899 --> 00:00:40,239
So everyone's just calling it the 'Huawei
ban.'

15
00:00:40,239 --> 00:00:44,660
To be fair, Trump's executive order doesn't
actually name Huawei.

16
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,719
But everyone knows who he’s talking about.

17
00:00:46,719 --> 00:00:48,829
It’s like that time in college when the
dining hall

18
00:00:48,829 --> 00:00:50,640
took away all the waffle makers

19
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:53,810
because somebody kept breaking in at 2am

20
00:00:53,810 --> 00:00:55,359
and stealing waffles.

21
00:00:55,359 --> 00:00:56,390
Dave.

22
00:00:56,390 --> 00:01:01,489
Anyway, Huawei is the world’s largest provider
of networking gear

23
00:01:01,489 --> 00:01:03,880
and the world’s number two smartphone vendor,

24
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,640
behind Samsung.

25
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:09,340
For years, congressional committees, the FBI,
the NSA,

26
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:11,920
and others have flagged close ties between
Huawei

27
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:14,220
and the Chinese Communist Party.

28
00:01:14,220 --> 00:01:16,700
Last year, the US government banned...

29
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:17,720
the US government...

30
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:19,940
from using equipment made by Huawei

31
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:23,000
and the other big Chinese telecom company,
ZTE.

32
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,840
That was over security concerns.

33
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:29,260
But the new executive order took that ban
a big step further.

34
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:33,050
First, Trump declared a "national emergency."

35
00:01:33,050 --> 00:01:34,050
And before you think,

36
00:01:34,050 --> 00:01:35,610
“Here Trump goes again,

37
00:01:35,610 --> 00:01:37,580
declaring another national emergency,”

38
00:01:37,580 --> 00:01:39,710
it’s actually pretty common.

39
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:42,610
Obama declared 13 national emergencies.

40
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:44,690
George W. Bush declared 14,

41
00:01:44,690 --> 00:01:47,170
and Clinton also declared 14.

42
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:49,660
So really, there are a lot more national emergencies

43
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:52,310
for President Trump to declare before his
term is up.

44
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:53,640
He’s probably got a list.

45
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:57,910
Anyway, here’s how Trump’s current national
emergency works.

46
00:01:57,910 --> 00:02:02,350
The Executive Order itself stops the use of
IT goods and services

47
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:05,430
from all companies subject to “foreign adversaries”

48
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:09,020
that pose “unacceptable risks” to national
security.

49
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:12,930
Then, the Commerce Department effectively
labeled Huawei

50
00:02:12,930 --> 00:02:16,370
as belonging to one of those “foreign adversaries”—

51
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:17,370
i.e.

52
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:18,370
China—

53
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:20,410
by putting Huawei and 72 of its affiliates

54
00:02:20,410 --> 00:02:24,200
on the Commerce Department’s “Entity List.”

55
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:27,000
The Entity List is a trade blacklist.

56
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,490
Anyone on it is barred from buying

57
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:30,810
parts and components from US companies

58
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:34,510
without getting the US government’s approval
first.

59
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:37,760
And that approval is no easy thing.

60
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,620
That's because the ban has a so-called

61
00:02:39,620 --> 00:02:42,000
"policy of presumption of denial."

62
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,660
Meaning, it's a no unless there's a really,

63
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:48,120
really good reason to say yes.

64
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,120
And \h"the U.S.

65
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,400
Government has determined that there is

66
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:53,250
reasonable cause to believe that Huawei

67
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:57,190
has been involved in activities contrary to
the national security

68
00:02:57,190 --> 00:03:00,630
or foreign policy interests of the United
States."

69
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:04,300
So I'm guessing Huawei purchases are generally
going to be a “no.”

70
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:07,810
"All the witnesses could you please raise
your hand

71
00:03:07,810 --> 00:03:12,570
if you'd use products or services from Huawei
or ZTE?

72
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:13,630
None of you would.

73
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:15,130
You obviously lead intelligence services,

74
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:17,150
so that's something of a biased question.

75
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:18,380
Raise your hand if you would recommend that

76
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,400
private American citizens use Huawei

77
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,470
or ZTE products or services?

78
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,880
None of you again are raising your hand.

79
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:25,959
Thank you for that."

80
00:03:25,959 --> 00:03:28,910
Senator Cotton raises an important point.

81
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:31,220
Or I assume he did because I was distracted

82
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,640
by the way that he kept mispronouncing Huawei.

83
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,560
It’s Huawei, with an H, people.

84
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,930
It’s not Wah-Wei.

85
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:40,760
Stop saying it like that!

86
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:41,920
Ahem.

87
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,140
Now if you're wondering what

88
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:46,290
the heads of US intelligence services know
about Huawei

89
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:48,610
that the average person does not,

90
