Ok, firstly, who keeps tires in a safe?

163
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:18,650
Secondly, what does a microchip company do
with tires, anyway?

164
00:07:18,650 --> 00:07:22,780
I think what we really need is a ban on stupid
metaphors.

165
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,840
Anyway, Huawei's CEO also insisted that Huawei

166
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,719
is totally ready for the ban—

167
00:07:27,719 --> 00:07:31,520
while also briefly noting that “the company's
annual revenue growth

168
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,409
may undershoot 20 percent.”

169
00:07:33,409 --> 00:07:35,990
That’s a lot to... “undershoot”.

170
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:39,660
It’s like, if you’re flying from New York
to San Francisco,

171
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,229
and you undershoot by 20%,

172
00:07:41,229 --> 00:07:44,110
you’ll end up in Battle Mountain, Nevada.

173
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:46,990
And no one wants to end up in Battle Mountain,
Nevada.

174
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,979
It’s the Armpit of America.

175
00:07:48,979 --> 00:07:52,860
And while Chinese media are saying 'there's
nothing to see here',

176
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:56,400
the Chinese Foreign Ministry sure is crying
foul.

177
00:07:56,400 --> 00:08:02,220
“We call upon the U.S. to stop using the
excuse of 'security issues'

178
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:05,389
to indiscriminately suppress Chinese companies,

179
00:08:05,389 --> 00:08:06,389
and provide a fair,

180
00:08:06,389 --> 00:08:10,289
just environment devoid of discrimination
for Chinese companies

181
00:08:10,289 --> 00:08:13,219
